<br>
2)  I wouldn't worry so much about PP right now.  You'll be more helped by improving your playing skills than by buying nice items.  If you want, however, you can explore the fascinating world of making jewelry.  This, I think, is how most enchanters get their money.  You may also want to try fighting orcs in high pass.  Shiny brass idol drops there, which is usually in high demand by higher level characters, so you can sell them for 50-60pp a pop in north fp.  And just so you know, I don't think I ever had more than 100pp at any given time until after my SK hit about level 45.  That was a long time ago, though, and even though he's level 60, I don't think I have more than 1kpp on all four of my characters combined.<br>
<br>
3)  It is possible to solo enchanters, as it is with all the classes.  Enchanters are one of the tougher classes to solo with, but if you know how to play one then soloing with them becomes fairly simple.  However, there is no doubt that enchanters are made for groups.  Groups work so much faster with a well-played enchanter in them.  You'll also find that the higher level you get, the harder it will become to get exp fast if you're soloing.  I started an enchanter a while ago (think he's lvl 21 now), and it seemed that exp started coming faster in groups starting around level 12ish.  <br>
