 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/upsykoth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Psykoth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=red><B>Dranalite<B></FONT></span><br>  Posts: 195<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/31/02 9:01:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2340.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hoc.phazed.org/~ralis/bond.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I have i guess newb questions</span><hr size=1> If you really want to do things solo, here's my recommendation...<br>
<br>
If you need cash, the best thing to do is find things that con green that carry weapons.  You can get up to 5gp for some rusty weapons, and it adds up pretty quick when you need spell money.  Also, another option is to start grouping in North Ro/West Commons/South Ro and kill Dervish Cutthroats.  They drop bronze, which sell to vendors for a few pp at a time.  <br>
<br>
Once you are in your mid-teens, head to Ocean of Tears and slaughter the Sisters of Erolisi.  They almost always drop a purity belt, which sells to vendors for around 5pp each, plus they can drop close to 1p in cash.  Once those go green, swim across to Spectre island and kill the gargoyles into your lower 20s.  They drop up to 3 stackable eyes, which sell for around 11pp each, and they drop them a LOT.  Don't worry about the wood elves hating you, because you can likely just illusion into a high elf (if you arent already) and sell at the top of the tower on the island just next to &quot;Sister Island&quot; where the Ancient Cyclops spawns.  BTW, when you finish killing gargs for the day, be sure to keep at least 1 up.  The skeletons on the isle are placeholders for a garg spawn, but luckily the gargs kill them on site, so leaving at least one up guarantees at least a full spawn when you return.<br>
<br>
As far as spells, once you hit lvl 12 and get Languid pace, you should always have a slow spell up while you are solo.  You don't have many hit points, and your pet has even less.  A hasted pet and slowed monster will be much easier for you to kill, but still expect to jump in and tank (take damage) for your pet.  Whenever you pull a monster, pull it with slow instead of tash (unless it is known to be really resistant).  Let it hit you, then back away slowly to let pet get aggro.  Once he's got it, toss your DoT (damage over time) spell on the monster, then engage the monster with melee/nukes.  Use root to keep the monster in place, because it makes it easier for you to step in and tank for your pet, then step away when you need to bandage yourself.<br>
<br>
You'll be mid-20s after the gargoyles go green, and from there you can choose to head to popular places like Lake of Ill Omen or South Karana, but you'll know your limits of what you can handle if you decide to continue solo'ing.  At level 29 you can hand your pet an extra weapon for him to dual wield, which increases his damage output by around 70%.<br>
<br>
If you have specific questions, feel free to look me up in game.<br>
<br>
Regards,<br>
<br>
Psykoth<br>
